  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nA client should know about an up-coming fork. When a VC is building subscriptions for a future slot, it should ensure that the subscription does not cross a fork-boundary in which case the signature for a future slot will be invalid. \r\n\r\nThis is important in determining whether a validator is an aggregator or not. \r\nSimilarly, when subscribing to subnets and/or deciding on the current number of aggregate validators existing for a subnet on a particular slot, the future fork needs to be taken into account. ",
